{"escalations": {"t1+t4": {"model": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4.5", "output": "Based on the retrieved public context:\n\n**Orionfold Arena** is the cockpit for running, comparing, and scoring local models with a leaderboard. According to the product description, \"Orionfold Arena is a single-screen cockpit for running, comparing, and scoring local language models on one NVIDIA DGX Spark,\" displaying GPU telemetry, published models, benchmark measurements, and a leaderboard built from your own results.\n\nRegarding separation of concerns: Yes, scoring should stay separate from training/export evidence. The retrieved context establishes this architectural principle explicitly: \"**Advisor** is the flagship model product\" while \"**Workbench** is the build/govern/operate environment that creates and proves artifacts.\" The Workbench integrates \"Arena + fieldkit + Cortex + lane/eval/training receipts\" as distinct operational layers. Training/export evidence (like NeMo Framework field notes documenting training performance) belongs in the training/export receipt layer, while Arena handles the evaluation and scoring cockpit function on the local machine.\n\nCitations: [product_orionfold_arena, spec_orionfold_local_ai_workbench_v1]", "score": {"alias_residue": false, "bare_answer": false, "citation_ok": true, "cited_source_ids": ["product_orionfold_arena", "spec_orionfold_local_ai_workbench_v1"], "passed": true, "private_state_risk": false, "refusal_ok": true, "route_ok": true, "strict_passed": true, "thinking_leak": false}, "status": "ok", "tier": "T4", "usage": {"completion_tokens": 261, "cost": 0.003251, "prompt_tokens": 1946}}}, "expected_behavior": "answer", "family": "unsloth_arena_partner_path", "retrieval_top1_score": 45.003251, "retrieval_top1_source": "spec_orionfold_local_ai_workbench_v1", "route": {"escalate": true, "hosted_egress_blocked": false, "private_state_query": false, "trigger": "citation_rank_sanity"}, "routed_t1+t3": {"alias_residue": false, "bare_answer": false, "citation_ok": true, "cited_source_ids": ["product_orionfold_arena"], "passed": true, "private_state_risk": false, "refusal_ok": true, "route_ok": true, "strict_passed": true, "thinking_leak": false}, "routed_t1+t4": {"alias_residue": false, "bare_answer": false, "citation_ok": true, "cited_source_ids": ["product_orionfold_arena", "spec_orionfold_local_ai_workbench_v1"], "passed": true, "private_state_risk": false, "refusal_ok": true, "route_ok": true, "strict_passed": true, "thinking_leak": false}, "routed_t1-only": {"alias_residue": false, "bare_answer": false, "citation_ok": true, "cited_source_ids": ["product_orionfold_arena"], "passed": true, "private_state_risk": false, "refusal_ok": true, "route_ok": true, "strict_passed": true, "thinking_leak": false}, "t1": {"alias_residue": false, "bare_answer": false, "citation_ok": true, "cited_source_ids": ["product_orionfold_arena"], "passed": true, "private_state_risk": false, "refusal_ok": true, "route_ok": true, "strict_passed": true, "thinking_leak": false}, "t1_output": "The Orionfold product that serves as the cockpit for running, comparing, and scoring local models with a leaderboard is Orionfold Arena, which is described as a single-screen cockpit for evaluating local language models on a DGX Spark and includes a leaderboard built from the user's own results. Scoring concerns should remain separate from training and export evidence because the Workbench is positioned as the environment that creates and proves artifacts, while Advisor functions as the flagship model product and the two are now distinct concerns.\nCitations: [product_orionfold_arena]", "task_id": "advisor-unsloth-arena-partner-path-0082"}
